8:
So now hear this, you who love pleasure and sit securely;
\q1 you who say in your heart, "I exist, and there is no one else like me;
\q1 I will never sit as a widow, nor will I ever experience loss of children."

\q1

15:
This is what they have become to you, those with whom you have worked, and you bought and sold with them when you were young,
\q1 and all of them keep doing their own foolish things;
\q2 and when you cry out for help, there is no one who can rescue you."
